	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=11706&mid=105608117615143>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=11706&mid=105608117615143>few notes on bard aggro</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=11706&mid=105608117615143#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Jun 20th 12:34 AM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=234823><span id= >buvasthebard</span></a><br><span id=notbold>4 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>As a 57 bard, I can say that while we will never be #1 in either aggro or dps, we are up there.&nbsp;&nbsp;Yes, our melee dps sucks due to lack of dual wield.  Yes, because of this our melee aggro sucks.  However, as I found out tanking around the castle in PoD (now there was a challenge for a guy with &lt;1k ac and 2.2k hp), we can generate hella aggro with the right songs, and these same songs put me over 100 dps, which is ungodly for a bard if he wants to live in most groups :P.  If I was slowing and bardnuking I could hold aggro pretty well.  I wasnt the best tank, but we didnt wipe ever and I held aggro for most of the fights.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
